<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Godfather (Channel 13 Sunday at 1 p.m.): Francis Coppola's modern gangster 
classic, starring Marlon Brando. (4:00) 
</P>
<P>
The Lonely Passion of Judith Hearne (Bravo Sunday at 5 p.m.): Maggie Smith is 
brilliant and heart-breaking as a desperate Irish spinster thrown into 
spiritual crisis. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Passport to Pimlico (Channel 28 Wednesday at 1 p.m.): Classic British comedy in 
which the discovery of an ancient treaty leads a small group of people to set 
up their own country in the heart of London. Stanley Holloway and Margaret 
Rutherford star. (1:30) 
</P>
<P>
Scarface (AMC Saturday at noon): The raw, brutal Howard Hawks 1932 original, in 
which Paul Muni plays an Al Capone carbon. (1:30) 
</P>
<P>
The Last Waltz (Channel 7 Saturday at 1 a.m.): Martin Scorsese brought an 
unprecedented intimacy and power to the concert film in this 26-song look at 
the last appearance of The Band, at the time (1978), America's most 
distinguished rock group. (2:00) 
</P>
</TEXT>
