<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Spanning the era of two world wars, "Till We Meet Again" is a Judith Krantz 
story about the adventures of three women and the men in their lives. 
</P>
<P>
The two-part, five-hour CBS miniseries can be seen 9 to 11 p.m. Sunday, with 
the conclusion airing 8 to 11 p.m. Tuesday on Channels 2 and 8. 
</P>
<P>
The cast includes, clockwise from top left, Mia Sara as actress Delphine de 
Lancel, Michael York as her father, Lucy Gutteridge as her mother, Barry 
Bostwick as flight instructor Terence McGuire, Bruce Boxleitner as pilot Jock 
Hampton and Courteney Cox as flier Freddy de Lancel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Mia Sara, Michael York, Lucy Gutteridge, Barry Bostwick, Bruce 
Boxleitner and Courteney Cox. Tony Esparza; Bob Greene of CBS 
</P>
