<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRUNES EXHUMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re Richard Cromelin's Nov. 5 Introducing column: In discussing the band Gavin 
Friday and the Man Seezer, Cromelin implied that the Virgin Prunes group was no 
longer in existence. Mary D'Nellan, a member of the Virgin Prunes, wrote to us 
on Oct. 3: "We've been recording in Dublin all summer -- our new record is 
coming out in Europe next week. . . . It's called "Nada" and we're all very 
proud of it. . . ." 
</P>
<P>
For a band about which so little information is available, a bit of 
misinformation in a newspaper as widely read as The Times can be very harmful. 
</P>
<P>
ARIEL C. ROSENTHAL 
</P>
<P>
Claremont 
</P>
<P>
JENNIFER H. SIMPSON 
</P>
<P>
Upland 
</P>
</TEXT>
