<HEADLINE>
<P>
AN ACTIVE ALLIANCE OF CHEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Nov. 5 cover story presents a distorted impression of the Women's Culinary 
Alliance. 
</P>
<P>
Support organizations such as the alliance, founded by chef Elka Gilmore and 
several other high-profile chefs, provide opportunities for members to learn 
from each other's trials and successes. It is unfortunate that in many such 
groups those who have become the most successful no longer take the time to 
participate. 
</P>
<P>
Happily, the Women's Culinary Alliance counts among its members many 
hard-working chefs -- some high-profile and some working for their stars and 
toques -- as well as a wide variety of food industry professionals. 
</P>
<P>
DEBBIE SLUTSKY 
</P>
<P>
President 
</P>
<P>
The Women's Culinary Alliance 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
