<HEADLINE>
<P>
AN END TO CHARITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In their Nov. 5 letters, Elizabeth Gaines and John Termini expressed disgust at 
the treatment of animals in the filming of "The Bear." I agree completely with 
them. 
</P>
<P>
I was glad to learn from an editorial note at the end of their letters that the 
Fund for Animals and the Wildlife Fund had endorsed this film; I am now closing 
the trust funds I have established for each of these supposedly humane groups. 
I regret that for 30 years I have contributed generously to both. 
</P>
<P>
I have been in the motion-picture industry for 40 years and have witnessed the 
way humane officers are dealt with on sets. The film makers simply tell him or 
her to "take a walk" when they plan a cruel shot, so the humane officer does 
not see it. 
</P>
<P>
E. L. FULLERTON 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
