<P>
* Over at New Visions, Taylor Hackford is mulling the purchase of a biker 
script. 
</P>
<P>
* Not to be out-revved, Sylvester Stallone (who once took Barbara Walters for a 
spin on his bike) has a biker project in hand, according to a source. 
</P>
<P>
* And Walter Hill's got another biker pic on the boards called "American Iron." 
</P>
<P>
 Don't expect any of these films to mention the most famous of the outlaw bike 
gang. The Hell's Angels have their name and logo under copyright and trademark 
protection. Pat H. Broeske and Kirk Honeycutt 
