<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE: FRIEDEN UND FREIHEIT: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Patrick Goldstein 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Graham Nash's last solo album featured a barbed broadside about the Berlin Wall 
titled "Over the Wall." After the historic events of the past week, Nash feels 
the song is more timely than ever. So he's rushed Steve Stills and David Crosby 
into the studio to redo the song's vocals, CSN style. Nash says the song will 
be out as a single within 10 days. "We're signed to Atlantic, so I'd like them 
to put it out," he said. "But if they don't want to get involved, we'll just 
press up 1,000 copies and send them out to radio ourselves." Nash added that 
CSN will begin recording a new album in January, with a proposed April release 
date, to be followed by a four-month summer concert tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
