<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE: DRUM BOOGIE: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK GOLDSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Is it possible -- a rock album without guitars, keyboards or electronics of any 
kind? It's been done, thanks to Siouxsie Sioux and her drummer pal, Budgie, who 
have taken time off from Siouxsie &amp; the Banshees to make an all-percussion 
album under the moniker of the Creatures. Titled "Boomerang," the record 
features percussion, Siouxsie's vocals and a Budgie-propelled melange of bells, 
chimes and muted trumpets. Due at month's end from Geffen Records, it offers 
such songs as "Pluto Drive," "Speeding," "Killing Time" and "Strolling Wolf." . 
. . And Bryan Adams is still in the studio working on his new album -- he's 
switched producers from Steve Lillywhite to Mutt Lange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
