<HEADLINE>
<P>
TORNADO-HIT ALABAMA DECLARED DISASTER AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush declared Friday that a major disaster exists in the state of 
Alabama, clearing the way for federal aid to repair the damage caused by a 
killer tornado earlier last week. 
</P>
<P>
The tornado hit Nov. 8 and cut a four-mile-long swath of destruction through 
Huntsville, Ala., killing at least 17 people and injuring at least 463. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
