view of the 600-foot-long tunnel, cut through the belly of the Exxon Valdez by 
removing 1,600 tons of steel, looking toward the tanker's bow. ; Photo, Whole 
sheets of the ship's skin are shredded, twisted and crumpled. BRUCE K. HUFF / 
Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
