<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO S.D. COUNTY BLAZES BATTLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One brush fire burned some 50 acres and another at least 150, but no 
firefighters were hurt fighting the two blazes Saturday, California Department 
of Forestry officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Crews contained the first fire, which began about 1:10 p.m., to some 50 acres 
in Rice Canyon, a mile east of Interstate 15 and about six miles south of the 
Riverside County line, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Some 200 firefighters contained the blaze without damage to any structures, 
including a hut in the area full of dynamite, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Some 275 firefighters, meanwhile, hoped today to contain the second fire, which 
has burned 150 acres southwest of Lake Wohlford, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire, which began about 3 p.m., was only 35% contained by late Saturday 
night and reportedly was near buildings in the rural area east of Escondido, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
No people were threatened, however, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
