<P>
YOUTH'S SLAYING CALLED GANG-RELATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old San Diego youth was killed early Saturday morning in an apparent 
gang-related Mira Mesa shooting, San Diego police said. 
</P>
<P>
Raymond L. Jose was shot about 12:20 a.m. near the intersection of Reagan Road 
and Mira Mesa Boulevard, as he approached a dark-colored car, police and 
coroner's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
After the shooting, Jose's companions carried him to a nearby fast-food store, 
where paramedics arrived but found him dead, police said. 
</P>
