<TEXT>
<P>
NASA technicians struggled to make up 12 hours in lost time to keep the space 
shuttle Discovery on schedule for the start of its countdown to a launching 
Wednesday on a secret military mission. Work to fix a booster control unit and 
a hydraulic leak led to the delay. The countdown was scheduled to begin at 4 
p.m. today, the same time that the shuttle's crew was expected to arrive at the 
Kennedy Space Center in Florida for final preparations. 
