<HEADLINE>
<P>
MASKED ASSAILANTS BEAT ARAB WOMAN TO DEATH IN GAZA STRIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Masked assailants stabbed and beat an Arab woman to death Saturday, hospital 
officials said. Palestinian reporters in the Gaza Strip said she was suspected 
of immoral behavior and of providing assistance to Israeli authorities. 
</P>
<P>
The hospital officials identified the woman as 40-year-old Atiyat Inajar and 
said she died of her wounds at Nasser Hospital in the Israeli-occupied Gaza 
Strip town of Khan Yunis. 
</P>
<P>
The Israeli military command confirmed the death and said the woman's death is 
under investigation. 
</P>
<P>
Separately, Arab doctors said troops opened fire to disperse stone-throwing 
Palestinian youths in the Gaza village of Beit Hanoun and the Shati refugee 
camp, wounding 11 protesters aged 16 to 23. 
</P>
<P>
The army command said it had no information about the incidents. 
</P>
<P>
Isa Ali Sabah, 29, of the village of Khadr, near Bethlehem, died at East 
Jerusalem's Mukassed Hospital on Saturday after suffering head injuries when 
stones were thrown at his car in the West Bank last month. Israel Radio said 
that Sabah lost control of his car during the assault and it crashed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ISRAEL -- TERRITORIES AND POSSESSIONS; PALESTINIANS -- ISRAEL; ARABS -- ISRAEL; 
GAZA STRIP; MURDERS -- ISRAEL 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111989-0138 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 137102 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 19, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
