<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY'S 'ESSENCE' CAPTURED ON PAPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Long Beach is abandoning its old logo, a drawing of City Hall, for a slicker 
image of rolling waves and skyscrapers. The design was chosen from 137 entries 
in a logo contest, and the winner, Paul Showalter Design of San Gabriel, will 
receive $5,000. 
</P>
<P>
Mayor Ernie Kell said the logo captures the "essence of Long Beach. It depicts 
the meeting of an important urban center with the ocean." 
</P>
<P>
The new logo will be used on city publications, stationery and signs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
