<HEADLINE>
<P>
DUCKS SINK BEAVERS, 30-21, TO WIN THE BATTLE OF OREGON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EUGENE, Ore. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Derek Loville and Terry Obee made the big plays in the final quarter Saturday 
as the Oregon Ducks beat archrival Oregon State, 30-21, to wrap up their best 
season in a quarter of a century. 
</P>
<P>
Loville rushed for 111 yards and scored two touchdowns and Obee caught six 
passes for 125 yards and one score as the Ducks finished the season at 7-4 
overall and 5-3 in the Pacific 10. Even though the record is Oregon's best 
since the Ducks went 7-2-1 in 1964, they aren't expected to get a postseason 
invitation. Oregon hasn't been to a bowl game in 26 years. 
</P>
<P>
Oregon State is 4-6-1 and 3-4-1 with a game remaining next Saturday at Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
The Beavers trailed 16-0 at halftime but rallied to pull within 23-21 on a 
24-yard scoring pass from backup quarterback Nick Schichtle to Pat Chaffey with 
7:51 to play. 
</P>
<P>
Then Loville, who moved up to No. 10 on the Pac-10 career rushing list, scored 
on a two-yard run to make it 30-21 with 4:41 left. 
</P>
<P>
Oregon's Bill Musgrave completed 19 of 38 passes for 267 yards to break the 
single-season passing yardage record set by Chris Miller in 1986. Musgrave, a 
junior, passed for 2,761 yards this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
