</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yonder, bouncing back from his loss in the Young America last month, won the 
$242,800 Remsen for 2-year-olds by three-quarters of a length over Roanoke at 
Aqueduct in New York. 
</P>
<P>
In the $182,400 co-featured Demoiselle Stakes for 2-year-old fillies, 
Rootentootenwooten won in a driving finish, upsetting the favored Bookkeeper. 
</P>
<P>
Roanoke, ridden by Jose Santos and carrying 122 pounds, had a clear lead 
entering the stretch but could not hold off the charge of Yonder, ridden by 
Eddie Maple. 
</P>
