<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARVARD FALLS IN WATER POLO SEMIFINAL, 13-3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harvard High's hopes for a third consecutive trip to the Southern Section water 
polo final came to a quick end Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded El Toro scored on its first three shots en route to a decisive 13-3 
win over the fourth-seeded Saracens in a 3-A Division semifinal game at Santa 
Monica High. The win puts the defending 3-A champions into Wednesday's title 
game against Capistrano Valley, a 7-6 winner over Marina in the other 
semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
"We just didn't play well at all," Harvard Coach Rich Corso said. "This was an 
old-fashioned butt kicking. We were tentative the first 14 minutes." 
</P>
<P>
El Toro Coach Don Stoll instructed his team to put early pressure on Harvard 
All-American goalie Larry Bercutt. 
</P>
<P>
While El Toro was shooting bullets at Bercutt, the Saracens weren't even firing 
blanks at Charger goalie Eric Terwilliger. 
</P>
<P>
"We didn't even take a shot until the end of the second quarter," Corso said. 
"We just weren't aggressive enough." 
</P>
<P>
El Toro (25-5) built a 6-0 lead before Hasan Yardimci got Harvard (27-5) on the 
scoreboard 55 seconds before halftime. But any thoughts of a comeback were 
dashed in the third quarter as the Chargers scored four unanswered goals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
