<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOOKLET AVAILABLE ON REMOVAL OF ASBESTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Contractors State License Board wants to help consumers learn to identify 
asbestos and be aware of precautions to take in its removal. 
</P>
<P>
Asbestos cleanup of more than 100 square feet requires certification by the 
state. Even if the work is done by a homeowner, state regulations apply. 
</P>
<P>
Asbestos, a naturally occurring mineral fiber, can cause asbestosis and cancer. 
Asbestos has been used in vinyl floor tile, vinyl sheet flooring, patching 
compounds, textured paints, ceilings, stove and furnace insulation, pipe 
insulation, wall and ceiling insulation, appliances, roofing, shingles and 
siding. 
</P>
<P>
For a free copy of its 12-page booklet, "A Consumer Guide to Asbestos," send a 
self-addressed envelope to the board at P.O. Box 26000, Sacramento, Calif. 
95826. A current list of contractors certified by the state to engage in 
asbestos-related work can also be requested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
